From eaae9b81637a8cadc98ac6dffd8a5c30deb930c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@becurious.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:03:27 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add weekly Audit view with student, teacher, idle, and branch
 tabs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a Daily view / Audit view toggle next to the Attendance week
picker. The audit view provides four tabs for visual schedule
checking:

1. Students — every student with scheduled vs needed count, day-by-day
   breakdown showing which car and time, pickup status. Summary cards
   for fully scheduled, partial, missing, and missing pickups.

2. Teachers — workload per teacher per day, max-per-day warnings,
   list of unscheduled students per teacher. At-max indicators.

3. Idle / Waste — detects teacher idle time: riding in the car with
   no assignment (teacher swap detours, gaps). Shows total wasted
   minutes per teacher with impact bars and event details.

4. Branch summary — per-branch overview of students, sessions needed
   vs scheduled, coverage %, car capacity per day, and the names of
   any unscheduled students.

All tabs have branch + teacher dropdown filters at the top.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
